<item>
            <title>[JDK-8316001] GC: Make TestArrayAllocatorMallocLimit use createTestJvm</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8316001</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>Make TestArrayAllocatorMallocLimit use createTestJvm (so that the test forwards VM/JAVA_OPTIONS). It seems there is no problem to propagate `-XX:+UnlockExperimentalVMOptions`.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Tested with:&lt;br/&gt;
`make run-test TEST=open/test/hotspot/jtreg/gc/arguments/TestArrayAllocatorMallocLimit.java` (PASS 1)&lt;br/&gt;
`make run-test TEST=open/test/hotspot/jtreg/gc/arguments/TestArrayAllocatorMallocLimit.java JTREG=&amp;quot;JAVA_OPTIONS=-XX:+UnlockExperimentalVMOptions&amp;quot;` (PASS 1)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Started hs_tier1-5 to see that we do not propagate conflicting flags.</description>
